ontentSummary xml:lang="nl"><![CDATA[Forensic intelligence experts play an essential role in various businesses and organisations. The Netherlands Forensics Institute, the police and intelligence agencies are well-known places where students in the forensic track can continue their career. There are also many other companies developing systems for the judicial field. Banks, insurance companies, and all other large organisations increasingly have to deal with the consequence of (cyber)crime.]]></contentSummary><contentType>website</contentType><subject>job perspective</subject><webLink xml:lang="nl"><![CDATA[http://studieadres.nl]]></webLink></contentLink><programDescription xml:lang="nl"><![CDATA[The Forensics track aims to make you a specialist in forensic intelligence. As a forensic analyst, you are responsible for tracing digital evidence on all levels, from a single computer to a large network. What activities were performed? Which errors were intentionally made and where were they hidden? Are certain files missing and where can they be found? To answer these kind of questions, you need the profound knowledge this Master has to offer. Not only will you be able to track down cybercrime, you will also learn how to document your evidence in a way that others can understand and will even hold up in court.]]></programDescription><programDescription xml:lang="en"><![CDATA[The Forensics track aims to make you a specialist in forensic intelligence. As a forensic analyst, you are responsible for tracing digital evidence on all levels, from a single computer to a large network. What activities were performed? Which errors were intentionally made and where were they hidden? Are certain files missing and where can they be found? To answer these kind of questions, you need the profound knowledge this Master has to offer. Not only will you be able to track down cybercrime, you will also learn how to document your evidence in a way that others can understand and will even hold